# Personal, per-developer provisioning hooks are not shared: they are optional,
# machine-specific, and may contain secrets (e.g. claude-config-seed/). Ignore
# the directory's *contents* rather than the directory itself...
local/*

# ...but DO track the committed example templates, so a colleague who clones the
# repo can see the hook contract and copy a starting point. (Re-includes need
# the parent dir not fully excluded, which is why the rule above is `local/*`
# and not `local/`.) Every `*.example` file is tracked; `README.example.md`
# needs its own line since it does not end in `.example`.
!local/*.example
!local/README.example.md
